      <item>
        <title>Category pages not working / 404</title>
        <dc:creator><![CDATA[mburridge]]></dc:creator>
        <description><![CDATA[
            <p>Hi <a class="mention" href="https://community.frontity.org/u/rob_cal_uk">@rob_cal_uk</a></p>
<p>There isn’t a default for <code>categoryBase</code>. If you leave it out of your configuration in <code>frontity.settings.js</code> and look at the state you’ll see that it’s just an empty string. I think the problem was that you had the <code>Category base</code> set in the WP admin, so you also needed it in your Frontity configuration.</p>
<p>I’m glad you managed to get it working. <img src="https://community.frontity.org/images/emoji/apple/raised_hands.png?v=9" title=":raised_hands:" class="emoji" alt=":raised_hands:"></p>
          <p><a href="https://community.frontity.org/t/category-pages-not-working-404/4579/14">Read full topic</a></p>
        ]]></description>
