      <item>
        <title>Category pages not working / 404</title>
        <dc:creator><![CDATA[mburridge]]></dc:creator>
        <description><![CDATA[
            <p>Hi <a class="mention" href="https://community.frontity.org/u/rob_cal_uk">@rob_cal_uk</a></p>
<p>I’ve cloned your repo and managed to get it working.</p>
<p>Try adding a <code>categoryBase</code> property to the <code>wp-source</code> settings in <code>frontity.settings.js</code>.</p>
<pre><code class="lang-javascript">{
      "name": "@frontity/wp-source",
      "state": {
        "source": {
          "url": "https://wp.robcallaghan.co.uk",
          "categoryBase": "/blog/category"
        }
      }
    }
</code></pre>
<p>The value here will be what you define in <code>Settings</code> → <code>Permalinks</code> → <code>Category base</code> in the WordPress admin.</p>
<p>Let me know how you get on. For more info <a href="https://api.frontity.org/frontity-packages/features-packages/wp-source#state-source-categorybase">see here</a>.</p>
          <p><a href="https://community.frontity.org/t/category-pages-not-working-404/4579/12">Read full topic</a></p>
        ]]></description>
